-- Problem (LaTeX):
/-
How many positive perfect squares less than $2023$ are divisible by $5$ ? $\textbf{(A) } 8 \qquad\textbf{(B) }9 \qquad\textbf{(C) }10 \qquad\textbf{(D) }11 \qquad\textbf{(E) } 12$
-/

-- Solution/Answer (LaTeX):
/-
Since $\left \lfloor{\sqrt{2023}}\right \rfloor = 44$ , there are $\left \lfloor{\frac{44}{5}}\right \rfloor = \boxed{\textbf{(A) 8}}$ perfect squares less than 2023 that are divisible by 5.
-/

import Mathlib.Tactic

theorem wiki_index_php_a7066294f1 : Prop := by
  sorry
